</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[281,1677,367,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
Allied to the common and widely distributed 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiedemann" authorityName="Wiedemann" box="[1201,1676,679,719]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Glipa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis box="[1201,1444,679,719]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Glipa tricolor</emphasis>
Wiedemann
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the form of the elytral markings and the more thinly pubescent and shining underside with but little white pubescence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
